se different environments for political expression and action, Bishara illuminates how expression is always grounded in place—and how a people can struggle together for liberation even when they cannot join together in protest.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aPalestinian ArabszIsraelxPolitics and government. 0aPalestinian ArabszWest BankxPolitics and government. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / Middle Eastern Studies.2bisacsh  aPalestine.  acommemoration.  aembodiment.  amilitarism.  apolitical expression.  aprison.  aprotest.  apublic culture.  aresistance.  asettler colonialism.40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503632103423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503632103/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles